-- Bertelsmann says buys Time interest in Bookspan
-- 
-- Tue Apr 10, 2007 4:44am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/10/us-bookspan-bertelsmann-announcement-idUSWEN626120070410

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - DirectGroup Bertelsmann, the global direct-to-consumer division of Bertelsmann AG BERT.UL, said on Tuesday it had purchased from Time Warner Inc.'s ( TWX.N ) Time Inc. its 50 percent share of Bookspan. 

 Bookspan, which was established in 2000 as a partnership between the two companies, owns and operates 40 book clubs in the United States including Doubleday Book Club, Literary Guild, Book-of-the-Month Club and special interest and lifestyle clubs. Terms of the transaction were not announced. Bookspan will be integrated into BMG Columbia House, an operating unit of DirectGroup that markets music and DVDs direct to consumers in the United States and Canada through such market-leading brands as BMG Music Service and Columbia House DVD Club.